Ensure we close any existing ssh connection in testGerritConnection

Upgrade Apache Commons Collections to v3.2.2

Version 3.2.1 has a CVSS 10.0 vulnerability. That's the worst kind of
vulnerability that exists. By merely existing on the classpath, this
library causes the Java serialization parser for the entire JVM process
to go from being a state machine to a turing machine. A turing machine
with an exec() function!

https://web.nvd.nist.gov/view/vuln/detail?vulnId=CVE-2015-8103
https://commons.apache.org/proper/commons-collections/security-reports.html
http://foxglovesecurity.com/2015/11/06/what-do-weblogic-websphere-jboss-jenkins-opennms-and-your-application-have-in-common-this-vulnerability/

Ensure we close any existing ssh connection in testGerritConnection
Readme updates.

Fixed NullPointerException in ViewGerritChainResultsAction. Used
component imports to resolve AutoWire issues with commentService and
deploymentProjectService.
Support for Bamboo 5.10.0-5.10.3
5.8.0-5.9.10 readme udpates.
5.8.0-5.9.10 Support updates.
Minor version bump.
SDK updates for Bamboo 5.7 - 5.7.2.
Version bump for Bamboo 5.7.
Bamboo-5.7.0 Support. Web repository updates.
Support for merging Gerrit branches.
Readme updates for Bamboo 5.6
Bamboo 5.6.0 enhancements. Removed depricated class BranchDetectionCapableRepository and replaced with BranchInformationProvider. Added capability to create branches if needed.
5.10-5.5.1 support. Resolved default MetaConfig path setting where null-null would be created in path. Resolved permission issues on MetaConfig path.
Remote agent fix, only local server runs the gerrit monitor thread.
Remote repository trigger enhancements.
Readme updates.

Updates to resolve the following branch issues:

gReview probelm - bamboo is checking out master branch #30
How to restrict bamboo to poll the changes only on a particular branch #26

You can now configure which branch to poll, master, 'All Branches', or specify a custom branch of your choice. Otherwise, you can leave the new default setting, master, and just use Bamboo's features for maintaining builds for specific branches.
Updates for branch builds supporting 5.1.0-5.5.0.
Misc updates for supporint 5.1.0-5.4.1. Updated README for branch support.
Added support for pulling changes by branch.
Added capability for listing local and remote branches.
Added functionality to support getOpenBranches. Added support for manually building specific branches by context, plan branches in the UI.
Added additional missing dependencies for support up to 5.4.1.
Removed depricated AdministrationConfigurationManager. Added new reference.
